  • Allow extra travel time as services will be very busy, and plan ahead using the Trip Planner to see if your travel is affected.

urlText: Ferries will be busy during Vivid Sydney
content:
Ferry customers are advised to expect delays and long queues for ferries to and from the city during Vivid Sydney from Friday 24 May to Saturday 15 June. Services will be busy and are expected to reach capacity from mid-afternoon, particularly on weekends. Some additional ferries will run on weeknights and weekends during the event.
 
Vivid Sydney attendees planning to catch a ferry to precincts around Circular Quay, Barangaroo or Pyrmont should plan ahead and have a back-up transport option in mind, from most wharves you can catch buses to the city or to nearby train stations to continue your trip.
 
Ferries in the harbour will also be affected by Vivid Sydney Drone Shows taking place on the evenings of Saturday 8, Sunday 9 and Saturday 15 June. Ferries will not run to or from Circular Quay from 9pm to 9.30pm on these dates. F1 Manly ferries will drop off and pick up from Barangaroo wharf instead, other ferry routes will run to an altered timetable arriving and departing Circular Quay before 9pm and after 9.30pm.
 
Visit the Vivid Sydney event page for more details on transport services during the event.

urlText: Circular Quay diversions during Vivid Sydney
content:

Buses that usually run to and from Circular Quay will start and end trips at Martin Place instead while roads are closed for the event at the following times:

  • Sundays and Monday public holiday (10 Jun) from 5pm to midnight
  • Saturdays and long weekend Sunday (9 Jun) from 5pm to 1am

  • Catch trains or continue on foot to travel between Martin Place and Circular Quay during these times.
  • Allow extra travel time and check signs at bus stops for the alternative stop locations.
  • Visit the Vivid Sydney event page for more transport details.
 
Missed stops:

  • Museum of Sydney, Phillip St (200059)
